🚀 DSA Roadmap for Beginners (Python)

Think of DSA like a game with levels. You don’t jump to boss fight (DP) on day 1.

🟢 LEVEL 1: Basics (Foundation — MUST STRONG)
🔹 Topics
Time & Space Complexity (Big-O)
Arrays & Strings
Basic Python tricks (very important)
🔹 Notes (Simple)
Big-O
O(1) → constant (best)
O(n) → linear
O(log n) → binary search type
O(n²) → nested loops (avoid when possible)
Arrays
Stored in contiguous memory
Fast access: arr[i]
Strings
Immutable in Python
Use slicing, [::-1], etc.
🔹 Must Learn Patterns
Two pointers
Sliding window
🔹 Python Cheat
# reverse string
s[::-1]

# frequency count
from collections import Counter
Counter(arr)
🟡 LEVEL 2: Core Data Structures
🔹 Topics
Linked List
Stack
Queue (Deque)
🔹 Notes

Linked List

Node → data + next
No index access
Good for insert/delete

Stack (LIFO)

stack = []
stack.append(10)
stack.pop()

Queue (FIFO)

from collections import deque
q = deque()
q.append(10)
q.popleft()
🔹 Important Problems
Reverse linked list
Valid parentheses (stack)
Implement queue
🔵 LEVEL 3: Recursion + Backtracking
🔹 Topics
Recursion basics
Backtracking
🔹 Notes
Function calls itself
Always define:
Base case
Recursive case
🔹 Example
def factorial(n):
    if n == 0:
        return 1
    return n * factorial(n-1)
🔹 Backtracking = try → fail → undo
Subsets
Permutations
🟣 LEVEL 4: Searching & Sorting
🔹 Topics
Binary Search
Sorting algorithms
🔹 Notes

Binary Search

Works only on sorted array
def binary_search(arr, target):
    l, r = 0, len(arr)-1
    while l <= r:
        mid = (l+r)//2
        if arr[mid] == target:
            return mid
        elif arr[mid] < target:
            l = mid+1
        else:
            r = mid-1
🔴 LEVEL 5: Trees
🔹 Topics
Binary Tree
BST
🔹 Notes
Tree = hierarchical
Traversals:
Inorder
Preorder
Postorder
⚫ LEVEL 6: Graphs
🔹 Topics
BFS
DFS
🔹 Notes

DFS (Recursion)

def dfs(node):
    visited.add(node)
    for n in graph[node]:
        if n not in visited:
            dfs(n)

BFS (Queue)

from collections import deque
